---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro'
import { site } from '../lib/site'
---

<Page title="CV · Serina McFall" description="Curriculum vitae for Serina McFall: software developer, accessibility-first, Auckland-based.">
  <article class="cv">
    <p class="download-bar">
      <a href="/serina-mcfall-cv.pdf" download="serina-mcfall-cv.pdf" class="download-btn">
        Download CV (PDF)
      </a>
    </p>
    <header class="cv-head">
  <div>
    <h1>Serina McFall</h1>
    <p class="role">Software Developer · accessibility-first · neurospicy</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="contact">
    <li><a href={site.url}>vixenz.dev</a></li>
    <li><a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></li>
    <li><a href="tel:+64214672266">+64 21 467 266</a></li>
    <li><a href={site.github}>GitHub</a></li>
    <li><a href={site.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a></li>
    <li>{site.location}</li>
    <li>NZ citizen</li>
  </ul>
</header>

 <section>
  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>Software Developer. I've made the shift from nearly a decade in customer service to a career in tech.</p>
  <p>I came into Dev Academy with no prior coding knowledge. The biggest thing I've learned is how to code, and I've also learned to better understand myself, my needs, and how I think. As well as Human Skills: the empathy and understanding others I built up over a decade in customer service, and the team craft I found in Dev Academy. Tech is the industry I can see still being viable in the next 20 years, and I love it: server-side gives structure to the side of my brain that needs it, and my artistic side loves the design of the front end. I found the home I did not know I was looking for.</p>
  <p>I'm neurodivergent, and I've learned this is not a weakness but is in fact a strength I can use. I plan and doc before I write code, I gate WCAG 2.2 AA on my own projects, and I start Dev Academy's AI Launchpad on 27 July 2026: 16 weeks of agentic coding plus industry placement.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Experience</h2>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Bachcare, The Holiday Home Company</h3>
    <p class="job-meta">Auckland, NZ (Hybrid) <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span> Dec 2021 to Apr 2026</p>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Feedback and Owner Operations Specialist <span class="role-dates">Dec 2022 to Apr 2026</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Owned guest feedback resolution, sitting between the guest's needs and the owner's constraints to land solutions that worked for both.</li>
        <li>Trained new team members on how to run feedback: what the role actually involves, and how to stay empathetic to guests who are frustrated.</li>
        <li>Supported the owner relations team day to day: maintenance escalations, guidance for owners on improving their guest stays, and general problem-solving.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Booking Management Specialist <span class="role-dates">mid-2022 to Dec 2022</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Managed in-stay needs for holiday-home guests: maintenance escalations, booking changes, and cancellations. Coordinated with third-party providers to keep stays on track.</li>
        <li>Handled the complex booking scenarios other agents escalated: last-minute swaps, multi-property groups, disputed changes.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Reservations Specialist <span class="role-dates">Dec 2021 to mid-2022</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Booked guests into properties across Bachcare's holiday-home portfolio, matching their preferences to what each property could actually deliver.</li>
        <li>Provided pre-stay support so guests arrived knowing what to expect: property specifics, access, and local context.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>TIC Group</h3>
    <p class="job-meta">Auckland, NZ (On-site) <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span> May 2018 to Dec 2021</p>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Claims Coordinator</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Ran the warranty claims lifecycle for JB Hi-Fi's faulty products: raised claims, handled supplier paperwork, and saw them through to settlement so JB got their money back.</li>
        <li>Owned salvage operations for TIC's NZ division: ordered containers, built picklists, and coordinated pickup and shipping to the Auckland port. Faulty hardware went to AU for sale overseas as parts.</li>
        <li>Day to day: TIC Reporter (a bespoke Java logistics tool), Excel, and Word. Handled logistics coordination with couriers and freight-forwarders.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>JB Hi-Fi</h3>
    <p class="job-meta">Auckland (Sylvia Park, then Botany) <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span> Nov 2010 to May 2018</p>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Counter Coordinator <span class="role-dates">Botany <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span> ~Nov 2013 to May 2018</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Led the counter team of 5: ran schedules, did one-on-ones, and was the person they came to when they needed a manager to step in.</li>
        <li>Bridged counter staff and management as their in-between: took team concerns up and management decisions back down.</li>
        <li>Kept the counter running day to day alongside the team-lead work: customer service, POS, cash handling, and the escalations that came my way.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="role">
      <h4>Customer Service Representative <span class="role-dates">Sylvia Park, then Botany <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span> Nov 2010 to ~Nov 2013</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Joined the Sylvia Park store as part of the team that opened it on day one, then transferred to Botany two years in.</li>
        <li>Travelled to Christchurch for a week to help set up and open the new store there, on the strength of my Sylvia Park launch experience.</li>
        <li>Day to day: counter sales, POS, cash handling, finance applications, and returns coordination with distributors.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Projects</h2>
  <ul class="projects">
    <li>
      <h3>Moonlit Library</h3>
      <p class="project-meta">
        <a href="https://moonlit-library.onrender.com">moonlit-library.onrender.com</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
        <a href="https://github.com/serina-mcfall/moonlit-library">github.com/serina-mcfall/moonlit-library</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Stack:</strong> Express + Knex + SQLite on the server and React + Vite on the client</p>
      <p><strong>Role:</strong> Solo build</p>
      <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> This was a Dev Academy challenge that earned three credentials (CP02 + WD03 + WD04). It's a personal library designed for how I read and has been deployed on Render.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Atlas: a visual concept library</h3>
      <p class="project-meta">
        <a href={`${site.url}/work/atlas`}>vixenz.dev/work/atlas</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
        <a href="https://github.com/serina-mcfall/atlas">github.com/serina-mcfall/atlas</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Stack:</strong> React + Vite + TypeScript, Express + Knex + SQLite, MDX</p>
      <p><strong>Role:</strong> Solo build (in progress)</p>
      <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> This project was a rework of a Dev Academy challenge called Art Gallery. I have reworked it into an accessibility-first concept library that holds both concept sheets and reference sheets through kind-based routing. WCAG 2.2 AA is gated in Playwright tests. So far four concept sheets are shipped in the repo (React Components, How a database query travels, useState vs useReducer, and What aria-modal actually does), along with a Terminal reference sheet.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Kiwicom: a developer project discovery hub</h3>
      <p class="project-meta">
        <span class="deploy-note">not yet deployed</span>
        <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
        <a href="https://github.com/Oscar-Wakefield-Ngahuru-2026/Kiwicom">github.com/Oscar-Wakefield-Ngahuru-2026/Kiwicom</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Stack:</strong> React + Vite + TS + Tailwind, Node + Express + TS, PostgreSQL (Supabase auth), Knex</p>
      <p><strong>Role:</strong> My role in this project was the git keeper of a 4-person team. I reviewed every PR, ran merges to Dev, and Resolved conflicts when they came about (luckily there were not many). 79 commits by the end, highest on the team.</p>
      <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> This was our Final Dev Academy group project. Kiwicom was built as a community hub for devs and uni grads to find open source projects that they can learn from as well as participate in. It pulls from GitHub and filters by language or topic, and lets them save projects as bookmarks. They can also build a profile page and add their own open source projects. We were able to ship browse, login, project pages, profiles, bookmarks, and create-project. We had planned for Claude-powered README summaries and deployment but these did not land before the assignment ended. We will likely keep working on this project as a group when time allows. The editorial design system (Lexend + JetBrains Mono, cream and deep-sky palette) is a reusable frontend layer, which came from my own aesthetic.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Realmstack</h3>
      <p class="project-meta">
        <span class="deploy-note">not deployed</span>
        <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
        <a href="https://github.com/Realmstacks/Realmstack">github.com/Realmstacks/Realmstack</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Stack:</strong> Cloudflare Workers (planning to bind D1, KV, R2, Queues), TypeScript. Rest of the stack still to be decided.</p>
      <p><strong>Role:</strong> Co-built with my husband. Currently in doc-led planning phase.</p>
      <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> This is a long-term worldbuilding project we are building together. We are in the declaration phase, so before code goes into the repo we have written the north-star vision, mapped out user flows and prior art, and done a deep encryption architecture research pass that pulled findings from multiple sources including Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, Kimi, and Deepseek to help lock our decisions early. Client-side end-to-end encryption is the technical anchor for the whole thing. This project was born of my original plan of a World Bible for my writing but morphed into a project that can be used by writers, D&amp;D Dungeon masters, Game writers and the like: a place where they can build out their world, find resources, and connect with other like-minded individuals to help in their creative endeavours. Though this started as my brainchild, my husband has taken my initial vision and breathed life into it, making it what it will eventually become.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Skills</h2>
  <dl class="skills">
    <div>
      <dt>Core</dt>
      <dd>
        <ul class="skill-list">
          <li>React</li>
          <li>TypeScript / JavaScript</li>
          <li>Node + Express</li>
          <li>Knex + SQL (SQLite, Postgres)</li>
          <li>HTML + CSS</li>
          <li>WCAG 2.2 AA + W3C APG patterns</li>
          <li>Playwright + axe-core</li>
          <li>Git</li>
          <li>Astro</li>
          <li>Vite + Vitest</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
    </div>
    <div>
      <dt>Familiar</dt>
      <dd>
        <ul class="skill-list">
          <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
          <li>Cloudflare Pages</li>
          <li>Supabase (Auth + hosted Postgres)</li>
          <li>MDX</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
    </div>
    <div>
      <dt>Learning next</dt>
      <dd>
        <ul class="skill-list">
          <li>Cloudflare Workers (D1, KV, R2, Queues)</li>
          <li>Agentic workflows</li>
          <li>Anthropic + OpenAI APIs</li>
          <li>Client-side E2EE</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Education</h2>
  <p><strong>Dev Academy Aotearoa — AI Launchpad</strong> — 16-week agentic coding programme: multi-agent workflows on production codebases, industry placement with a NZ tech company. 27 July – 13 November 2026.</p>
  <p><strong>Dev Academy Aotearoa</strong> — full-stack web development bootcamp. Completed 2026.</p>
  <p class="scaffold-note">[Phase 7 — add high school + partial fine arts degree; keep brief since Experience is rich.]</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Interests</h2>
  <p class="scaffold-note">[Phase 7 — art (Diamond Dots, resin, painting, digital), writing + worldbuilding (Avalune, D&amp;D, Magic), gaming, reading. Serina writes.]</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>References</h2>
  <p>Available upon request.</p>
</section>

  </article>
</Page>

<style>

  .cv {
    max-width: 48rem;

  }

  .download-bar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .scaffold-note {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-ui);
    color: var(--mist);
    opacity: 0.65;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--tile-border);
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .download-btn {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-ui);
    color: var(--moonlight);
    background: var(--surface-card);
    backdrop-filter: blur(var(--surface-card-blur));
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: box-shadow 200ms ease, transform 200ms ease;
  }

  .download-btn:hover,
  .download-btn:focus-visible {
    box-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(232, 180, 196, 0.35);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .download-btn:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--magnolia);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .download-btn {
      transition: none;
    }
    .download-btn:hover,
    .download-btn:focus-visible {
      transform: none;
    }
  }

  .cv-head {
    display:flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--tile-border);
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;

  }

  .cv-head h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;

  }

  .role {
    color: var(--mist);
    font-size: var(--text-ui);


  }

  .contact {
    list-style: none;
    text-align: right;
    font-size: var(--text-ui);
    color: var(--mist);

  }

  .contact a {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 4px 0;
}

  .cv .projects, .cv .other {
    list-style: none;
    display:grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;

  }

  .cv .projects li, .cv .other li {
    color: var(--mist);
    max-width: none;

  }

  .cv .projects h3 {
    color: var(--moonlight);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .cv .project-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--mist);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .cv .project-meta .deploy-note {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .cv .projects p {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .cv .projects p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cv .projects strong {
    color: var(--lotus);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }

  .cv section {
    margin: 1.25rem 0;

  }

  .cv h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--lotus);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  .cv .job {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cv .job:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cv .job h3 {
    color: var(--moonlight);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.15rem;
  }

  .cv .job-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--mist);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .cv .role {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--tile-border);
  }

  .cv .role:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cv .role h4 {
    color: var(--moonlight);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .cv .role-dates {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--mist);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .cv .role ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .cv .role li {
    color: var(--mist);
    max-width: none;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .cv .role li::before {
    content: "·";
    color: var(--lotus);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .cv dl {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cv dl div {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .cv dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--lotus);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cv dd {
    color: var(--moonlight);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .cv .skill-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: inline;
  }

  .cv .skill-list li {
    display: inline;
    color: var(--moonlight);
  }

  .cv .skill-list li:not(:last-child)::after {
    content: " · ";
    color: var(--lotus);
    padding: 0 0.15rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 36rem) {
    .cv-head { flex-direction: column; }
    .contact { text-align: left; }
    .cv dl div { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  @media print {
    .download-bar,
    .scaffold-note {
      display: none !important;
    }
    :global(.atmosphere) {
      display: none !important;
    }
    :root {
      --midnight: #ffffff;
      --moonlight: #1a1a1a;
      --mist: #444;
      --lotus: #444;
      --lantern: #444;
      --magnolia: #444;
      --tile-border: #ccc;
      --deep-sky: #ffffff;
    }
    :global(body) {
      background: white !important;
      color: black !important;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    :global(body > header),
    :global(body > footer),
    :global(.skip-link) {
      display: none !important;
    }
    :global(main) {
      padding: 0 !important;
    }
    .cv {
      max-width: 100%;
    }
    .cv a {
      color: #1a1a1a;
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .cv-head {
      padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .cv-head h1 {
      font-size: 1.65rem;
    }
    .cv section {
      margin: 0.9rem 0;
    }
    .cv h2 {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .cv .projects, .cv .other {
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .cv .projects h3 {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
    }
    .cv .project-meta {
      color: #444;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }
    .cv .projects p {
      margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    }
    .cv .projects strong {
      color: #444;
    }
    .cv .job {
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }
    .cv .job h3 {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .cv .job-meta {
      color: #444;
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }
    .cv .role {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      padding-left: 0.5rem;
      border-left-color: #ccc;
    }
    .cv .role h4 {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    }
    .cv .role-dates {
      color: #444;
    }
    .cv .role ul {
      gap: 0.2rem;
    }
    .cv .role li::before {
      color: #444;
    }
    .cv .skill-list li:not(:last-child)::after {
      color: #444;
    }
    .cv dl {
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }

</style>